******
[4] Cholera - Zimbabwe (Mashonaland West)
Date: Tue 21 Oct 2008
Source: Associated Press (AP) [edited]
<http://ap.google.com/article/ALeqM5jYaMdvfd4B2f0SL_hy9UM7heD0-QD93UT2280>


Zimbabwean health authorities say 11 people have died from cholera in
a town outside Harare in an outbreak blamed on collapsing sewer
services and the country's economic crisis.

Authorities said Tuesday [21 Oct 2008] at least 500 people have been
treated since the outbreak earlier in October 2008 in Chinhoyi, 70
miles (113 km) northwest of Harare.

Diarrhea outbreaks in impoverished towns across the country have been
blamed on water outages and other problems associated with Zimbabwe's
economic meltdown. Authorities have urged the government to stem the
discharge of sewage from broken pipes into rivers and dams.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Chinhoyi is located in Mashonaland West as can be seen on a map of
